:0},{"w":"Covered","s":228.64,"e":230.04,"line":36},{"w":"with","s":230.04,"e":230.46,"line":36},{"w":"prophecy","s":230.46,"e":231,"line":36},{"w":"Ooh","s":233.4,"e":233.42,"line":37}],"lines":[{"s":10.96,"e":29.2,"text":"St. John's keeps time with weathered hands."},{"s":29.2,"e":38.82,"text":"If the walls of the FBI block the light that tries to rise."},{"s":39.96,"e":44.26,"text":"Over the brick, over the door, you can't bury what came before."},{"s":44.56,"e":48.96,"text":"Oh, this church with a steady flame, I hear the warning call its name."},{"s":49,"e":53.84,"text":"And when the shadow leans too long, the ground starts singing like a song."},{"s":53.84,"e":59.28,"text":"You can stack your steel up high, but the truth won't stay tonight."},{"s":60.66,"e":66.04,"text":"If the light gets blocked, the towers rise."},{"s":70.84,"e":75.34,"text":"St. John still speaks through dust and sand."},{"s":75.42,"e":78.18,"text":"St. John's Soup Kitchen."},{"s":78.18,"e":83.1,"text":"Covered with prophecy."},{"s":83.82,"e":85.82,"text":"Covered with prophecy."},{"s":89.34,"e":93.06,"text":"On marked steps and chipstone stairs."},{"s":94.68,"e":97.72,"text":"People bring their hunger there."},{"s":98.74,"e":102.2,"text":"Soup in bowls and folded coats."},{"s":103.4,"e":107,"text":"Quiet prayers and battered notes."},{"s":108.44,"e":112.88,"text":"If the watchers crowd the sky and seal the morning from our eyes."},{"s":112.9,"e":117.58,"text":"There's a name carved deep in time and it won't be erased tonight."},{"s":117.66,"e":122.26,"text":"You can pair the dark with stone, you can name the night your own."},{"s":122.26,"e":129.04,"text":"But the old bells know the way through the fear and through the grave."},{"s":129.04,"e":134.38,"text":"If the light gets blocked, the towers rise."},{"s":139.44,"e":143.7,"text":"St. John still speaks through dust and sand."},{"s":143.76,"e":146.42,"text":"St. John's Soup Kitchen."},{"s":147.56,"e":148.86,"text":"Covered with prophecy."},{"s":153.14,"e":154.54,"text":"Ooh."},{"s":162.86,"e":167.46,"text":"Let the first red ray come back."},{"s":168.18,"e":172.26,"text":"Oversoot and broken tracks."},{"s":172.26,"e":180.26,"text":"What was fed to every soul will not be lost to what they hold."},{"s":181.1,"e":184.6,"text":"And if they build, let them build."},{"s":185.44,"e":189.28,"text":"The old words outlast the chill."},{"s":189.98,"e":194.18,"text":"I hear new words say it clear."},{"s":194.94,"e":199.22,"text":"The dawn is still here."},{"s":202.26,"e":207.14,"text":"If the light gets blocked, the towers rise."},{"s":212.16,"e":216.28,"text":"St. John still speaks through dust and sand."},{"s":216.42,"e":219.02,"text":"St. John's Soup Kitchen."},{"s":220.22,"e":221.48,"text":"Covered with prophecy."},{"s":224.36,"e":226.24,"text":"Covered with prophecy."},{"s":228.64,"e":231,"text":"Covered with prophecy."},{"s":233.4,"e":233.42,"text":"Ooh."}],"duration":242.39999389648438,"source":"whisper","generatedAt":"2026-05-22T02:24:44.795Z","model":"whisper-1"}